%U A394099 82,1849,121,129,529,2209,94,343,125,289,169,2809,106,265,106,361
%N A394099 Largest composite number m with n <= m <= n^2 such that the largest divisor of n*m not exceeding sqrt(n*m) is equal to n.
%C A394099 a(n) = max X_n, where X_n = {m composite : n <= m <= n^2 and g(n*m) = n} and g(k) = A033676(k) is the largest divisor of k not exceeding sqrt(k).
%C A394099 a(n) = n^2 if and only if n is prime; for composite n, a(n) < n^2.
%C A394099 X_n is nonempty for all n >= 2, so a(n) is well defined.
%F A394099 a(n) = n^2 if and only if n is prime.
%e A394099 n=3: the composite m in [3,9] with g(3m)=3 are 4, 6, 9; the largest is 9 = 3^2, so a(3)=9.
%e A394099 n=4: the largest composite m in [4,16] with g(4m)=4 is 8 (m=9 fails since g(36)=6), so a(4)=8.
%t A394099 g[k_] := Max[Select[Divisors[k], #^2 <= k &]];
%t A394099 a[n_] := Max[Select[Range[n, n^2], CompositeQ[#] && g[n #] == n &]];
%t A394099 Table[a[n], {n, 2, 57}]
%o A394099 (Python)
%o A394099 from sympy import isprime, divisors
%o A394099 def g(k): return max(d for d in divisors(k) if d*d <= k)
%o A394099 def a(n): return max(m for m in range(n, n*n+1) if not isprime(m) and g(n*m) == n)
%o A394099 print([a(n) for n in range(2, 58)])
